      • insertOrderItem

        public int insertOrderItem(OrderItem orderItem)
        This method inserts a new entry in the "orderitem" table. If an entry with the same id_order as the one passed as the parameter is found, the method updates the "order" table, specifically the entry with the same id as the id_order and then inserts the new entry in the "orderitem" table. If an entry with the same id_order and prod_name as the one passed as the parameter is found, the method updates the "order" table, specifically the entry with the same id as the id_order and updates the quantity of the entry that was found to be similar to the argument.
        Parameters:
        orderItem - : OrderItem
        Returns:
        0 in case of successful insert/update or a negative number otherwise
